<img class=" wp-image-1346572 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/HIV-AIDS.png?resize=640%2C431&#038;ssl=1" alt="Kano to enrol 553 HIV/AIDS patients to access free healthcare services — Official" width="640" height="431" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/HIV-AIDS.png?resize=300%2C202&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/HIV-AIDS.png?resize=58%2C39&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/HIV-AIDS.png?resize=260%2C175&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/HIV-AIDS.png?resize=193%2C130&amp;ssl=1 193w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/HIV-AIDS.png?resize=115%2C77&amp;ssl=1 115w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/HIV-AIDS.png?resize=560%2C378&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/HIV-AIDS.png?w=617&amp;ssl=1 617w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Kano State Government is to enrol 553 people living with HIV/AIDS to access free healthcare services, Aminu Bello-Sani, the Public Relations Officer, Kano State Agency for the Control of Aids (KSACA) disclosed in a statement on Monday, in Kano. According to him, the Executive Secretary of the state’s Contributory Healthcare Management Agency (KSCHMA), Dr Halima Mijinyawa revealed this when she paid a courtesy visit to the Director General (DG) of (KSACA). Mijinyawa said that the enrollment of the HIV/AIDS patients was part of their allocation for integration into the state’s basic healthcare provision fund, and for the attainment of Universal healthcare coverage in the state. The KSCHMA executive secretary was at the Agency to inform the KSACA DG on their resolution for the selection of the eligible beneficiaries, and the criteria for the enrollment. She explained that the Basic Health Provision Fund is a Federal Government intervention under the equity programme of the contributory health care scheme. Mijinyawa added that the aim of the fund was to provide free healthcare services to pregnant women, children under five, the elderly, poorest of the poor, and people living with disability. Earlier, the KSACA DG, Dr Sabitu Shanono said the integration of HIV/AIDS into the programme was a welcome development as the global HIV/AIDS response was on the decline. He commended the KSCHMA, but also pleaded with them to increase the number of HIV/AIDS patients into the programme. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria Kano State Government is to enrol 553 people living with HIV/AIDS to access free healthcare services, Aminu Bello-Sani, the Public Relations Officer, Kano State Agency for the Control of Aids (KSACA) disclosed in a statement on Monday, in Kano. According to him, the Executive Secretary of the state’s Contributory Healthcare Management… December 22, 2020 In "Health" Governor  Abdullahi Ganduje of Kano State has approved the employment of 50 medical doctors to be deployed across the 44 Local Government Areas of the state. This is contained in a statement by Aminu Bello-Sani, the Public Relations Officer (PRO), Kano State Agency for the Control of Aids (KSACA), on… December 2, 2020 In "News" By Abdulmumin Murtala - Kano 4,734 People With Disabilities (PWD) will benefit from the Kano State Government Vunerable Health Care Scheme. This was announced by the Executive Secretary, Kano State Contributory Health Care Management Agency (KSCHMA), Dr Halima Muhammad Minjinyawa at the engagement meeting with PWDs on Basic Healthcare Provision… December 17, 2020 In "News"